1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. e3 Bg7 4. Be2 O-O 5. O-O d6 6. b3 Nbd7 {[%cal Ge7e5] The most popular move. Black wants to get the typical King's Indian break ...[e7]-[e5] in, and because of certain issues on the [a1]-[h8] diagonal, we can't really prevent the plan. However, it turns out that the resulting positions are positionally better for White. This is important info! Few players are aware of this.} 7. Bb2 e5 {The normal continuation. Why prepare the push even more, when it is possible to play right away? Well, some precaution is often suitable, also here!} 8. dxe5 Ng4 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Gg7b2] This is the tactical justification of Black's play. The [e5]-pawn is pinned and will be regained.} 9. c4 $1 {We use the time to improve our structure.} Ngxe5 {The most logical recapture.} ({•} 9... Ndxe5 10. Nxe5 Nxe5 {just transposes.}) ({•} 9... dxe5 10. h3 Nh6 {can hardly be recommended. After} 11. Qc2 Re8 12. Nc3 {White is much better, for instance,} e4 13. Nd2 f5 14. Rfd1 c6 15. c5 $1 Qe7 {has been played and now instead of sacrificing the c-pawn, White could have played the simple} 16. Bc4+ Kh8 17. b4 {with a good position. The knight can be regrouped with [Ne2].}) 10. Nxe5 ({I prefer this. The most popular is} 10. Nc3 {which is also not bad, but not as good!}) 10... Nxe5 ({Nobody plays} 10... Bxe5 $5 {A cool response is} 11. Bd4 $5 {followed by [Nc3].}) 11. Qd2 $1 {[%cal Gd2b2,Gf2f4]} ({Actually,} 11. Nc3 {is played much more often. [Qd2] is much stronger. It protects the [b2]-bishop and prepares the aggressive push [f2]-[f4] followed by exchanging Black's proud King's Indian bishop on [g7].}) 11... Re8 12. f4 $1 Ng4 ({Or} 12... Nd7 13. Bxg7 Kxg7 14. Nc3 {with a nice position.}) 13. Bxg7 Kxg7 14. Bxg4 Bxg4 15. Nc3 {[%cal Gc3d5,Gd2d4,Ga1e1] White has a pleasant advantage. The black kingside is severely weakened after the exchange of the dark-squared bishops. Black constantly needs to watch out for something like [Nd5] and [Qd4]+. Furthermore, White can advance with [e3]-[e4] and bring the [a1]-rook into play on the e-file. Fantastic potential!} *

