1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 c6 ({A favourite among Slav players. Black first consolidates the d5-pawn and prepares to develop the light-squared bishop to f5 or g4. Maybe the move c7-c6 isn't strictly necessary as preparation for the bishop sortie. Next, we will examine the direct} 3... Bf5 {(here and) 3...Bg4 (here) .}) 4. Bd3 {This prevents [Bf5].} Bg4 ({The natural continuation. The more modest Semi-Slav setup with} 4... e6 {is covered in the 3...e6 section.}) 5. Nbd2 {White intends to take back on [f3] with a knight. That's why I prefer to wait a little with the standard move [h2]-[h3].} Nbd7 {Very natural. Black just develops and even flirts with the active break [e7]-[e5]. It is no surprise that [Nbd7] is the most-played move. However White also has some possibilities!} 6. h3 {Now it is probably good to insert this little move.} Bxf3 7. Nxf3 {White has the bishops and should be happy. Only one idea can bother us.} Qc7 {[%cal Ge7e5] This is it. Black plans to strike in the centre with [e7]-[e5].} 8. Bd2 {An interesting subtlety.} ({The line after} 8. O-O e5 9. dxe5 Nxe5 {has scored well for Black although White of course is fine after something like} 10. Bd2 {.}) 8... e5 ({After the safe} 8... e6 {White gets the upper hand} 9. O-O Bd6 10. c4 { The bishops!}) 9. dxe5 Nxe5 10. Nxe5 Qxe5 11. Bc3 {The point of 8.Bd2 .} Qe6 {This is the best square for the queen.} 12. Qf3 {This works well against 11...Qd6 which is shown in the next trainable, but here it is less clear.} ({Maybe White should just play} 12. O-O {the engine gives a slight plus, but it looks pretty balanced.}) 12... Ne4 $1 {This is why the queen should be on [e6].} 13. Bxe4 dxe4 14. Qh5 (14. Qh5 {At first sight, this looks excellent for White. The bishop on c3 is much more active than Bf8 and the white queen might do some damage. If Black plays precisely the position is probably balanced, but with lots of play left. A sample line goes:} O-O-O $1 15. Rd1 Rxd1+ 16. Qxd1 f6 17. O-O Be7 18. Qh5 {. I would take White here because of the active queen, but objectively Black must be fine.}) *

