1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. e3 Bg4 {Black develops the bishop as active as possible and tries to save the move [c7]-[c6].} 4. Nbd2 {So we can take back on [f3] with the knight.} ({White could also play} 4. h3 {which is kind of the principled reaction. What I didn't like that much was:} Bxf3 $5 {, giving the bishop saves time and is tempting.} 5. Qxf3 e6 {Black is ready to play [c7]-[c5] with a sound position; and if} 6. c4 {, then apart from transposing to the 4. [e3] Slav with [c7]-[c6], Black can give a disturbing check:} Bb4+ {for instance} 7. Bd2 Bxd2+ 8. Nxd2 O-O {, and Black might get [c7]-[c5] in with good play.}) 4... Nbd7 {This can be met similarly as the mainline.} 5. h3 Bh5 6. g4 ({Here} 6. c4 {, followed by [Qb3] also looks attractive.}) 6... Bg6 7. Nh4 {[%csl Gg6] We gain the bishop pair.} e5 {Using the fact that Black played [Nbd7] and not [e7]-[e6].} ({The solid} 7... e6 8. Nxg6 hxg6 9. Bg2 {is comfortable for White. The bishops, the bishops!}) 8. Bg2 {White could also take on [e5], but this simple idea is very playable. We just develop and prepare short castling. Of course, sooner or later we will take on [g6] and gain the bishop pair.} Bd6 {Black keeps the tension, but it costs the [d5]-pawn.} 9. Nxg6 hxg6 10. g5 Nh5 11. Bxd5 {True, Black can win the pawn back because [g5] is hanging, but the white pieces becomes active.} exd4 {The best. Now Black gets the nice [f4]-square.} 12. exd4 {[%csl Gf4]} c6 13. Bf3 Qxg5 14. Qe2+ $1 {A disturbing check. White is ready to follow up with [Ne4], so the safest for Black is to allow an ending.} Qe7 15. Qxe7+ Kxe7 {Black could also take with the bishop, but capturing with the king is more logical, so the bishop can go to [f4].} 16. Nc4 Bf4 {White loses the bishop pair, still keeps the more comfortable position though.} 17. Bd2 Bxd2+ 18. Kxd2 {[%csl Gd4][%cal Gc2c3] White is slightly better in the ending. The pawn on [d4] gives a significant space advantage, next, we will protect it with [c2]-[c3]. The bishop on [f3] and the knight on [c4] exerts a lot of potential pressure on the black queenside.} *

