imple} 7. Be2 {, followed by short castle with a fine position.}) 7. dxc5 {Again, there are many other fine moves. The text simplifies into a nice IQP structure.} Nxc5 8. Bb5+ {Exchanging pieces is usually good, when you play against an isolated pawn because it reduces the opponents chances for building up a strong initiative as compensation for the long-term weakness.} Bd7 9. Bxd7+ Qxd7 10. O-O {[%csl Gd5][%cal Gb2b3,Gc1b2] White is better. With [b2]-[b3] and [Bb2] the bishop can become very active.} *

