ith a good game.} 8. a4 {So we prevent [b7]-[b5].} Be7 9. Nc3 O-O 10. Qe2 ({White could also start with} 10. Re1 {.}) 10... b6 {Keeping the tension is always a good option.} 11. d5 {We can already make this break.} ({Playing with the rook,} 11. Rd1 {, also makes sense.}) 11... exd5 12. Nxd5 Bb7 (12... Nxd5 13. Bxd5 Ra7 14. Rd1 Qc7 15. e4 {looks good for White.}) 13. Nxe7+ Qxe7 14. b3 {[%cal Gc1b2] Preparing [Bb2]. White is somewhat better. Black can try the radical:} Bxf3 $5 15. gxf3 ({If} 15. Qxf3 {, then} Ne5 {=}) 15... Ne5 {But after...} 16. Bb2 Nxc4 17. Qxc4 {[%csl Gb2] The bishop is strong.} *

