k needs to be careful.}) ({If} 6... Bf5 {, this move should be met by} 7. b4 {N which looks good for White.}) 7. O-O {[%cal Gb2b4] Next comes [b2]-[b4]. A plausible line goes:} g6 8. b4 Qd6 9. b5 ({We can already start playing forcing moves. Otherwise} 9. Bb2 {, intending [c3]-[c4] is also fine.}) 9... Ne5 10. Ba3 $1 {[%cal Ga3d6] Hitting the black queen.} Nxf3+ 11. Bxf3 Qc7 12. Nd2 $1 {[%csl Gc3] Giving a pawn for rapid development.} Qxc3 13. Nb3 {[%cal Ga1c1]} (13. Nb3 {Next comes Rc1 with great play. A sample line goes:} Qc7 14. Rc1 Qd8 15. Qd4 Bg7 16. Qe5 {, and Black hardly has any moves.}) *

