on} 6. dxc5 {can now be met by} Nxc5 {. However, in other lines, the black knight is not so well placed on [d7]. White has a very straightforward plan.}) 6. Nbd2 Bd6 {The typical move. The bishop is good here.} ({On} 6... Be7 {we play} 7. O-O O-O 8. Qe2 {, intending [e3]-[e4] with good play.}) 7. O-O O-O 8. Re1 $1 {[%cal Ge3e4] White wants to push [e3]-[e4].} Qc7 ({Or} 8... e5 9. e4 $1) 9. e4 $1 {White has the initiative.} dxe4 10. Nxe4 Nxe4 11. Rxe4 $1 {[%cal Ge4h4] The rook can go to the kingside.} Nf6 ({Safer is} 11... c4 12. Bc2 b5 {, but after} 13. a4 $1 {White plays all over the board.} b4 14. Rh4 f5 15. b3 $1 {The position will be opened which must be good for White.}) {After 13.Rh4 f5 is not so clear.} 12. Rh4 {[%csl Gh7] White has a strong attack.} g6 {More or less forced.} 13. dxc5 Bxc5 14. Bf4 {[%csl Gf6,Gg7,Gh6] White has a strong initiative. The dark squares around the black king are really weak.} *

