the king to safety before we start real action. Possible is} 6. Nbd2 {intending to meet} Bd6 {with the immediate} 7. dxc5 Bxc5 8. b4 {, but I prefer castling first.}) 6... Qc7 7. Nbd2 {The flexible...} b6 {...is met by...} 8. e4 $1 {[%cal Ge4e5] ...and White already has a serious initiative. In such direct lines, the extra move really matters! White is ready to play [e4]-[e5] with a lot of extra space and good attacking possibilities.} cxd4 9. cxd4 Nb4 ({Dangerous is} 9... dxe4 10. Nxe4 {}) 10. Bb5+ Bd7 {All this is well known with colours reversed, but again: the extra move matters!} 11. Bxd7+ Qxd7 {This has never been played. I guess White replies as follows.} 12. Ne5 Qb7 13. a3 Nc6 14. Nxc6 Qxc6 15. e5 {[%csl Gd4,Ge5] With a solid advantage based on space and better development.} *

