asy.} 12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Bxe4 Be6 ({Risky is} 13... f5 14. Bd5+ Kh8 15. b5 Ne7 16. c4 {White has scored 10.5/11 from here!}) 14. Re1 {[%csl Ge5] White has some nice pressure. Black's e-pawn is a concern. Later, we will try to improve our position with [a2]-[a3] and [c3]-[c4].} *

