 {. In this case, Black can force the play with dxe4} 13. Nxe4 Nxe4 14. Bxe4 f5 15. Bxd5+ Kh8 {, followed by [e5]-[e4] with good counterplay.}) 12... dxc4 {This is the safe solution.} 13. Nxc4 Bc7 14. Ncd2 {[%csl Ge4][%cal Gd1c2] White coordinates nicely. Next we can play [Qc2] with good control over the light squares. Please notice that [e5]-[e4] is always met by the smart [Bxf6].} *

