 {. In this case, Black can force the play with dxe4} 13. Nxe4 Nxe4 14. Bxe4 f5 15. Bxd5+ Kh8 {, followed by [e5]-[e4] with good counterplay.}) 12... e4 13. Bxf6 $1 {A nice intermediate move.} gxf6 {This ruins Black's kingside.} 14. cxd5 exf3 15. dxc6 fxg2 16. Kxg2 (16. Kxg2 {White is clearly better. Next comes Qh5. If} Qe5 {, then} 17. f4 $1 Qxe3 18. Rf3 Qe6 19. Rg3+ Kh8 20. Bxh7 $1 {decides.}) *

