e active} 8... dxc4 9. Nxc4 c5 {Doesn't solve all problems. White has several ways to keep some pressure. I would probably play...} 10. dxc5 bxc5 11. b5 {[%csl Gc4] With a strong knight on [c4] and a potential passed pawn on the queenside in an eventual ending.} ({The line with} 11. Qb3 cxb4 12. Qxb4 Qc7 13. Rc1 {also gives some initiatives.}) *

