{Better is} 12... h5 13. Nc2 {with a complex game, where White must be somewhat better because of the extra space in the centre.}) 13. cxd4 Nxd4 14. Bb2 Nc6 15. Rc1 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Gc1c7,Gb4b5] With great compensation. The pawn on [e5] makes it hard for Black to coordinate the pieces.} *

