1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. e3 Bg7 4. Be2 O-O 5. O-O d6 6. c4 {This is the principled continuation.} c5 (6... c5 {Always a popular move, if Black is ready to play a Benoni after} 7. d5 {.}) 7. Nc3 {In this repertoire we don't hurry to play [d4]-[d5].} Nc6 {OK, if we are provoked then we do it!} 8. d5 $1 {This is just good for White. The black knight is forced to an inferior square.} Ne5 9. Nxe5 dxe5 10. e4 {White is much better with space and superior structure. Compare this with 6...Nc6 .} *

