[GameId "2164710462161353"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. e3 Bg7 4. Be2 O-O 5. O-O d6 6. c4 {This is the principled continuation.} Nbd7 {Going for the legendary King's Indian Attack setup. I am pretty sure this is what you will face in at least 3 out of 4 games if Black is a King's Indian player, so it is a very important line. It also means that I will cover the other black setups a bit more lightly. Usually, it is White who plays the King's Indian Attack! It comes for instance after the moves 1.Nf3 d5 2.g3 Nf6 3.Bg2 e6 4.O-O Be7 5.d3 O-O 6.Nbd2 c5 7.e4 Nc6 8.Re1 b5 9.e5 Nd7 . Although, White has won some nice attacking games I sincerely believe that Black is absolutely fine - and I gave it to Black in my QGD course. So, playing it with an extra move is of course nice.} 7. Nc3 e5 ({If Black plays slow with} 7... c6 {then we will expand on the queenside} 8. b4 {with good play. Compare with the mainline.}) 8. b4 {White ignores Black's plan and starts active operations on the queenside.} Re8 {Preparing ...[e5]-[e4].} 9. Bb2 {Developing while waiting for Black to play the committal ...[e5]-[e4] move.} e4 10. Nd2 Nf8 {[%cal Gc8f5,Gh7h5,Gf8h7,Gh7g5] The standard move. Black wants to play [h5] and [Bf5] and [Nf8]-[h7]-[g5] and attack. Well, the attacking part we will come back to.} 11. a4 {Forward!} h5 12. a5 {Forward!} Bf5 {This ignores the white a-pawn.} 13. a6 $1 b6 {Taking on [a6] would leave Black with a terrible queenside.} 14. b5 {[%csl Gc6] Securing the [c6]-square. Then we can start dreaming of a knight there!} ({It is tempting to play} 14. d5 {with the idea [Nc3]-[b5]-[d4] in mind. However} Ng4 $1 {is pretty unclear} 15. h3 Nh6 {.}) 14... h4 15. h3 {Stopping the black pawn.} N8h7 16. f4 $1 ({I like to make it hard for Black on the kingside also. The engine just wants to play} 16. Na2 {with the eyes on the [c6]-square.}) 16... exf3 {Black has to open the position. If the kingside is blocked there is no counterplay at all.} 17. Bxf3 Rc8 18. e4 ({Maybe} 18. Re1 {was simpler. White is clearly better.}) 18... Be6 {This was Anton-Murzin, blitz 2021.} 19. Na2 {[%cal Ga2b4,Gb4c6] This is very strong. The knight goes from [a2] to [b4] and ends on [c6]. Simple and good! White is much better.} *

