[ECO "A80"]
[PlyCount "120"]
[GameId "2164710462530020"]

1. d4 f5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 d6 4. Nc3 g6 5. h4 $1 Bg7 6. h5 $1 Nxh5 7. Rxh5 $1 gxh5 8. Qxh5+ Kf8 {[%csl Gf8,Gh8][%cal Ge1c1] White has strong long-term compensation for the exchange. It is quite easy for White to develop the rest of the army and castle long, while Black's pieces will hardly ever be able to coordinate. Furthermore, the king is weak on [f8] and the [h8]-rook is out of play.} 9. Be2 {The most precise, but other moves were also good.} Nd7 $5 {A practical decision. Black gives the f-pawn, but gets the pieces out - well, some of the pieces.} (9... Qe8 10. Qh4 {and White can hit the black queen with [Bh5].}) 10. Qxf5+ Nf6 11. Qd3 c6 12. O-O-O {I think White is simply clearly better, maybe even strategically winning!} Be6 13. Nf3 b5 14. Ng5 ({Even better was} 14. e4 {for instance} Bc4 15. Qe3 Bxe2 16. Nxe2 {and the white knights will enjoy themselves on the kingside.}) 14... Bg8 15. Kb1 $6 ({Too soft. Again} 15. e4 $1 {was the way to go.}) 15... h6 $1 16. Nf3 Bh7 $1 {Black is fighting back.} 17. Qd2 ({Not} 17. e4 $2 b4) 17... a5 18. Rh1 $6 ({Correct was} 18. Bd3 {and White is somewhat better.}) 18... a4 19. Bd3 b4 20. Nd1 b3 21. Bxh7 Rxh7 22. cxb3 axb3 23. a3 Qa5 24. Qd3 Qd5 $6 ({Black was fine after} 24... Qb5 {.}) 25. Nc3 Qf7 26. Nh4 Kg8 27. Nf5 h5 28. f3 Nd5 29. Nxd5 cxd5 30. g4 $1 Rf8 $1 {Both players play well, but in time trouble Black misses something.} 31. Ka1 Kh8 $6 (31... Qe6 {was unclear.}) 32. Qxb3 $1 hxg4 33. Rxh7+ Kxh7 34. fxg4 Re8 35. Qc2 Kg8 36. Qg2 Bf8 37. Qh1 Rc8 38. a4 e6 39. Nh6+ Bxh6 40. Qxh6 Ra8 $2 {How often comes the decisive mistake on move 40?} (40... e5 $1 {holds according to the engine:} 41. dxe5 Rc1+ 42. Ka2 Qd7 43. b3 Qc7 {with sufficient counter threats.}) 41. b3 $1 Re8 42. Qg5+ Kh7 43. Bxd6 Qf1+ 44. Ka2 Qg2+ 45. Ka3 {White protects everything and wins easily.} Qh1 46. Qh5+ Qxh5 47. gxh5 Kh6 48. a5 Kxh5 49. Ka4 Kg4 50. a6 Kf3 51. Bf4 e5 52. Bxe5 Kxe3 53. Kb5 Kd3 54. a7 Ra8 55. Kb6 Kc3 56. Kb7 Rg8 57. a8=Q Rxa8 58. Kxa8 Kxb3 59. Kb7 Kc3 60. Kc6 Kc4 1-0

