1. d4 f5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 {The correct move-order.} d6 {Black could start with [d7]-[d6]. The intention is still to play [g7]-[g6] and [Bg7] and so on, but hopefully, avoid the raid by the white h-pawn.} 4. Nc3 {Keeping all options open.} e6 {Another flexible waiting move.} 5. Bd3 {[%csl Ge4] Just developing and taking control over [e4].} Nc6 {[%cal Ge6e5]} 6. Nf3 {We need to watch out for ...[e6]-[e5].} Nb4 ({If} 6... Be7 {then the offensive break} 7. e4 {is good for White.}) 7. Be2 {Keeping the bishop.} Be7 8. h3 {Securing the [f4]-bishop.} O-O 9. O-O (9. O-O {White is slightly better. Black can't get ...e6-e5 in. A sample line goes:} Nbd5 10. Nxd5 Nxd5 11. Bh2 {, followed by [c2]-[c4], and play on the queenside.}) *

