1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 {In this chapter we will meet some of Black's more rare lines.} b6 {This could be a prelude to a Queen's Indian setup.} 3. e3 {We do our usual stuff.} Bb7 4. Bd3 c5 {A reversed Reti.} 5. O-O d5 6. dxc5 {This is a promising change of the structure.} bxc5 7. c4 e6 {Black needs to protect the structure.} 8. cxd5 exd5 9. Bb5+ {A disturbing check.} Nbd7 {Entering the pin is dangerous.} 10. e4 $1 {White opens the position.} dxe4 11. Ne5 (11. Ne5 {Black is in big trouble. A sample line goes:} Qc7 12. Nxd7 Nxd7 13. Bf4 $1 Qc8 14. Nc3 Be7 15. Nd5 Bd8 16. Re1 {, and it will soon be curtains.}) *

