1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 {In this chapter we will meet some of Black's more rare lines.} b6 {This could be a prelude to a Queen's Indian setup.} 3. e3 {We do our usual stuff.} Bb7 4. Bd3 c5 {A reversed Reti.} 5. O-O g6 6. c4 {The most ambitious.} Bg7 7. d5 $1 {White has a good Benoni-strcuture because [Bb7] is shut out.} b5 {Tempting, but it doesn't really help.} 8. Nc3 $1 {It is important to keep the [d5]-pawn.} bxc4 9. Bxc4 O-O 10. e4 d6 11. Re1 (11. Re1 {Black has a really bad Volga gambit. A sample line goes:} Nbd7 12. h3 {nice prophylaxis. White prevents [Ng4]-[e5].} Nb6 13. Bf1 a5 14. a4 $1 {Securing the b5-square. White is much better.}) *

