1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 {In this chapter we will meet some of Black's more rare lines.} d6 3. e3 {It goes without saying that White had a bunch of other good moves!} Bg4 {It makes sense to get the bishop out. However, it doesn't make much sense to give it for the knight on [f3].} 4. Be2 ({This fits best with our repertoire. A very good move is also} 4. c4 {, followed by [Nc3].}) 4... Nbd7 5. h3 Bh5 {Giving the bishop for the knight is just handing White the bishop pair.} 6. c4 {This is the best setup.} e5 7. Nc3 Be7 8. Qb3 $1 {[%csl Gb7] Hitting [b7].} Rb8 9. g4 $1 Bg6 10. Nh4 {[%csl Gg6] Getting the strong black bishop.} Be4 {This has never been played, but is probably Black's best chance. Otherwise, White will just take on [g6].} 11. O-O (11. f3 Nh5 $1 {is the tactical justification.}) 11... h6 12. f4 (12. f4 {But White is better with a very active position. A sample line goes:} Bh7 {( Another line goes: 12...Nh7 13.Nxe4 Bxh4 14.c5! with a strong initiative. )} 13. Nf3 c6 14. f5 $1 {and the bishop is shut out from play.}) *

