1. d4 e5 {Just giving a central pawn can't be good.} 2. dxe5 d6 {Here it is important not to take on [d6] immediately. Instead, we fight for the initiative with active moves.} 3. Nf3 Bg4 4. Bg5 {Active and strong.} Qd7 5. Nc3 Bxf3 ({This apparently regains the pawn.Better is} 5... Nc6 {but after} 6. exd6 Bxd6 7. Ne4 $1 {White will take in [d6] or exchange queens with a big advantage.}) 6. gxf3 dxe5 7. Bh3 {A wake-up call. The mating threat on [d8] decides.} Qxd1+ 8. Rxd1 f6 9. Bc8 $1 {White is winning material.} *

