 moved the d-pawn once. 4.Bf4 White is just better. There is a juicy square on [e5].}) 4. Bg5 {Active development.} e6 {[%cal Gg5d8] This self-pins the knight which we immediately will exploit.} 5. e4 $1 fxe4 6. Nxe4 Be7 7. Ng3 ({Keeping all pieces on the board. Also fine was} 7. Bxf6 {.}) 7... O-O 8. Bd3 Nc6 9. Qd2 {Preventing [Nb4]. White is ready to castle long and start an attack or castle short and put pressure down the e-file. It is your choice! In both cases White is much better.} *

