ressure.}) 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 {Forced, otherwise the [e5]-pawn hangs.} 6. Nc3 f6 {This is a good setup. Compared to the positions where Black had played [g7]-[g6] and [Bg7], here there are more chances to equalize. Still, White can keep the game going with something like:} 7. a3 {Prevents [Bb4].} Be6 8. e4 (8. e4 {Maybe White still has a tiny practical edge. If} Bc5 {then} 9. Na4 {annoys the bishop.} Be7 10. Be3 {suddenly White is definitely better with long castling coming and control over [c5].}) *

