{Nobody has played} 5... Nb8 6. Nc3 {White is just better.}) 6. c4 {White has a favorable version of the typical King's Indian pawn structure. We welcome [Bxf3] because we gain the bishop pair and Black might be weak on the light squares later on. We also welcome the exchange of light-squared bishops, so sooner or later we will move the [f3]-knight and let Black take on [e2]. Then we will have the superior bishop because our central pawns are on the light squares.} *

